ert, Eat, Pray, Love #elizabeth gilbert  #eat pray love  #friend  #you  #unguarded  #book quotes  #books  #quotes  #book  #quote  #recognise  #yourself  #perspective   August 20 2015     /     1,041 notes     /     Permalink So many versions of just one memory, and yet none of them were right or wrong. Instead, they were all pieces. Only when fitted together, edge to edge, could they even begin to tell the whole story.  - Sarah Dessen, Just Listen #sarah dessen  #just listen  #memory  #right  #wrong  #truth  #story  #honesty  #pieces  #perspective   August 20 2015     /     4,316 notes     /     Permalink I for one like chaos. Chaos looks good on me.  - Ally Carter, Uncommon Criminals #ally carter  #uncommon criminals  #heist society  #chaos  #trouble  #book quotes  #books  #quotes   August 20 2015     /     58 notes     /     Permalink lexiwallman000 Asked Hi! do you know any books similar to Legend by Marie Lu? lexiwallman000 , Try these books: Noughts & Crosses (Noughts & Crosses, #1) - Malorie Blackman The Hunger Games (The Hunger Games, #1) - Suzanne Collins Gone (Gone, #1) - Michael Grant Shatter Me (Shatter Me, #1) - Tahereh Mafi Unwind (Unwind Dystology, #1) - Neal Shusterman The 5th Wave (The 5th Wave, #1) - Rick Yancey Enjoy the recommendations! :) #lexiwallman000  #book recs   August 20 2015     /     572 notes     /     Permalink Whether or not you believe in fate comes down to one thing: who you blame when something goes wrong. Do you think it’s your fault - that if you’d tried better, worked harder, it wouldn’t have happened? Or do you just chalk it up to circumstance?  - Jodi Picoult, Nineteen Minutes #jodi picoult  #nineteen minutes  #fate  #fault  #book quotes  #circumstance  #luck  #choice  #decision  #life  #belief  #book quote  #book  #quote   August 19 2015     /     1,000 notes     /     Permalink Love who you love while you have them. That’s all you can do. Let them go when you must. If you know how to love, you’ll never run out.  - Ann Brasha